title: Cameron Orr
text:
Cameron Orr (born 2 April 1995) is an Australian <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player who competes for the <a href="Melbourne%20Rebels">Melbourne Rebels</a> in <a href="Super%20Rugby">Super Rugby</a>. His usual position is prop.
Orr was originally part of the <a href="New%20South%20Wales%20Waratahs">Waratahs'</a> Generation Blue Academy and he played for the <a href="Greater%20Sydney%20Rams">Greater Sydney Rams</a> in the <a href="National%20Rugby%20Championship">National Rugby Championship</a>. In July 2016, Orr signed for English club <a href="Gloucester%20Rugby">Gloucester Rugby</a> to play in the <a href="Aviva%20Premiership">Aviva Premiership</a> from the 2016-17 season.
In February 2018, Orr returned home to Australia to play for <a href="Western%20Force">Western Force</a> as part of the <a href="World%20Series%20Rugby">World Series Rugby</a> invitational matches and the upcoming 2018 <a href="National%20Rugby%20Championship">National Rugby Championship</a> season.
Orr represented <a href="Australia%20national%20under-20%20rugby%20union%20team">Australia U20s</a> in both the 2014 and 2015 <a href="World%20Rugby%20Under%2020%20Championship">IRB World Junior Championships</a>, held in <a href="New%20Zealand">New Zealand</a> and <a href="Italy">Italy</a> respectively.
